711971f-a.text:
30th Street, south side, between Tenth and Ninth Avenues, showing the New York Central Station. The buildings to the left are on the north side of the street. This station was built in 1860 and remained standing until 1931.
May 13, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

710366f-a.text:
Ninth Avenue, north from W. 30th Street, as photographed from the downtown platform of the "El." The rear of the U. S. Post Office occupies the 31st - 32nd Street frontage. The loft structure at the S. E. corner of 31st Street houses the New York offices of the mail
order house--Sears Roebuck and Company.
June 7, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
